we have 3 sections in a lex program
	-declaration section
	-rule section 
	-main section
	
Functions:
	-yylex() - function to reade the input string and generate a sequence of tokkens
	
	-yywrap() - global variable , if the input is exhausted , it returns 1 otherwise it 	returns 0
	
	-yytext - points to the input string which is stored as temporary file
	
The default data type of input is string
	
	
	
	****	Lab programs	****
1- count the number of characters in the input string
2- count the number of words in the input string 
3- count the number of lowercase, uppercase , numerics, special characters and other characters in the input string
4- identify whether a identifier is valid or not
5- identify whether a number is even or odd
6- identify whether a number is perfect square or not (use -lm with gcc to use math library methods)
